Disable _FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64 in the generated config.h.

glibc 2.5 (Buffalo NAS) does not fully support _FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64 in all
code paths used by Samba.  After waf configure, edit the generated file
bin/default/include/config.h and comment out the define.

This is a post-configure, pre-build step (config.h is generated by configure
and not tracked by waf):

    sed -i 's|^#define _FILE_OFFSET_BITS 64|/* #undef _FILE_OFFSET_BITS */|' \
        bin/default/include/config.h

Expected result in config.h:
-  #define _FILE_OFFSET_BITS 64
+  /* #undef _FILE_OFFSET_BITS */
